struct  compare_edge
 A struct that provides the comparison of edge objects. It allows sorting of edges for priority queues. The sorting follows three rules: First, edges are sorted by ascending cost. Edges with the same cost are sorted preferring horizontal/vertical edges. Edges with same cost and orientation are sorted ascending by index position, i.e., first bottom to top, then left to right.
